 {"id":"franken_networkx-6n6e","title":"parity: filtered graph views should preserve adjacency() mapping contract","description":"restricted_view(...) and subgraph_view(...) currently yield adjacency() results as neighbor lists like [('a', []), ('c', [])] instead of the dict-like filtered neighbor mappings that NetworkX exposes. Upstream filtered views return adjacency iterators whose second item behaves like an atlas/mapping object. Match the upstream adjacency() iterator contract on both filtered graph view helpers.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:17:30.721444832Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T09:17:30.721444832Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
