 {"id":"franken_networkx-6r4x","title":"parity: Graph and DiGraph EdgeView should support set algebra","description":"Graph.edges and DiGraph.edges currently expose edge views that are not set-like. In FrankenNetworkX, operations such as G.edges | {('b', 'c')}, G.edges & {('a', 'b')}, G.edges - {('a', 'b')}, and G.edges ^ {('a', 'b'), ('b', 'c')} raise TypeError, while upstream NetworkX returns the expected edge sets. Match the upstream EdgeView set-algebra contract on Graph and DiGraph.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:50:53.633905734Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:26:18.327643520Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T05:26:18.325698038Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit 66b205e","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
